<div class="about-me-box about-me-pilot">
    <div class="row d-flex">
        <div class="col-md-6 align-self-center">
            <h2>I was an airline pilot.</h2>
            <p class="body-text">
                Prior to becoming a software engineer I was a professional pilot. I started flight training in 2010 at Liberty University. I earned my flight
                instructor certification while working on my aeronautics degree and started working for the school as an instructor. The regulations at the time required 1250 total hours of
                flight time to be hired by an airline. I built this time through instructing and a little bit of recreational flying.
                <br>
                I started at Piedmont Airlines in 2016 flying the Bombardier Dash-8. A couple years later transitioned to 
                the Embraer ERJ-145. My base airport was PHL.
            </p>
        </div>
